description:
Hey guys, this would've been up A LONG time ago but upon rendering I noticed a weird "green glitch" that showed up in playback (for example, look closely 2:09). There are actually numerous graphical glitches in this video alone. I re-rendered, altering the settings, ~5 times and to no avail, this green glitch keeps sporadically plaguing me. After doing a little research, I am thinking my [EVGA GTX 970] GPU may be the cause, although have no way to confirm. If ANYONE knows anything about this, please let me know. I use Powerdirector 11 when I render by the way. I'm just ready to be rid of this tomfoolery, ESPECIALLY after building a $2000 brand spanking new machine, highly disappointed right now.

Part 1: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dbD9Z0dJiGw
fulltitle: IT IS COMPLETE! | Building My PC (Part 2)
